From 9927256b916c8f54587aa611ee206fc30c3703cb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: MediLens Dev <dev@medilens.local>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 02:33:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: replace fake medicine scanning with real Claude AI
 vision + real AI chat

- backend/ai_service.py: Anthropic Claude integration for label scanning
  (vision) and grounded pharmacist chat, with defensive JSON parsing and
  graceful degradation when no API key is set
- backend/config.py: centralized pydantic-settings config (.env driven)
- POST /api/scan: new endpoint - uploads a photo, runs it through Claude
  vision, cross-checks allergies deterministically (defense in depth),
  persists medicine + auto-generated reminders, serves the photo back
  via /uploads
- POST /api/chat: now calls Claude with user profile + medication context,
  falls back to the original rule-based responses if AI is unavailable
- Fixed data-corruption bug: comma-delimited list storage broke on any
  warning text containing a comma (e.g. '4,000 mg'); switched to a safe
  '||' delimiter
- Flutter: added image_picker-based real camera/gallery capture in
  scan_tab.dart, wired through AppStateProvider.scanMedicineImage() to
  the new endpoint, with real error dialogs instead of a fake always-
  succeeds simulation
- Added MedicineImage widget to resolve scanned-photo URLs vs bundled
  demo assets across dashboard/detail screens
- Fixed 1500-second (25 minute) delay bug in the offline chat fallback
- api_service.dart: platform-aware backend base URL (10.0.2.2 for
  Android emulator, override via --dart-define=API_BASE_URL), typed
  ApiException with server error messages surfaced to the UI
- Added CAMERA/INTERNET permissions (Android) and camera/photo library
  usage descriptions (iOS)
- Added backend Dockerfile, .env.example, .gitignore
- Rewrote README with real setup/run/deploy instructions; removed the
  inaccurate 'backend complete' status doc
