-# medilens_ai
+# MediLens AI
 
-A new Flutter project.
+AI-powered medicine label scanner, medication reminder tracker, and pharmacist
+chat assistant. Flutter frontend + FastAPI backend, both backed by Claude
+(Anthropic) for the two AI features:
 
-## Getting Started
+| Feature | How it works |
+|---|---|
+| **Scan a medicine label** | Camera/gallery photo → `POST /api/scan` → Claude vision model reads the label → structured JSON (name, dosage, side effects, warnings, reminder times) → deterministic allergy cross-check → saved to DB → reminders auto-created |
+| **AI Pharmacist chat** | `POST /api/chat` → Claude, grounded with the user's profile (allergies, blood type) and active medications as system-prompt context → falls back to a rule-based responder if no API key is configured, so the app never hard-fails |
 
-This project is a starting point for a Flutter application.
+## Architecture
 
-A few resources to get you started if this is your first Flutter project:
+```
+lib/
+  models/        Plain Dart data classes (Medicine, Reminder, ChatMessage)
+  providers/      AppStateProvider — single source of truth, syncs to backend
+  services/       ApiService — all HTTP calls, platform-aware base URL
+  screens/        UI screens (scan, dashboard, chat, reminders, profile...)
+  widgets/        Shared widgets (MedicineImage resolves asset vs scanned photo)
 
-- [Learn Flutter](https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/learn-flutter)
-- [Write your first Flutter app](https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/codelab)
-- [Flutter learning resources](https://docs.flutter.dev/reference/learning-resources)
+backend/
+  main.py         FastAPI app, all REST endpoints
+  ai_service.py   Anthropic Claude integration (vision scan + chat)
+  config.py       Centralized settings (pydantic-settings, reads .env)
+  models.py       SQLAlchemy ORM models
+  schemas.py      Pydantic request/response schemas
+  database.py     SQLite engine/session setup
+```
 
-For help getting started with Flutter development, view the
-[online documentation](https://docs.flutter.dev/), which offers tutorials,
-samples, guidance on mobile development, and a full API reference.
+## Prerequisites
+
+- Flutter SDK 3.12+ (`flutter --version`)
+- Python 3.11+
+- An [Anthropic API key](https://console.anthropic.com/) — required for real
+  AI scanning; the app runs without one but scanning will return a clear
+  "not configured" error and chat drops to rule-based answers.
+
+## 1. Run the backend
+
+```bash
+cd backend
+python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate   # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
+pip install -r requirements.txt
+
+cp .env.example .env
+# edit .env and set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
+
+uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
+```
+
+Verify it's alive:
+
+```bash
+curl http://localhost:8000/api/health
+# {"status":"ok","ai_configured":true,"environment":"development"}
+```
+
+Interactive API docs: `http://localhost:8000/docs`
+
+### Docker alternative
+
+```bash
+cd backend
+docker build -t medilens-backend .
+docker run -p 8000:8000 --env-file .env medilens-backend
+```
+
+## 2. Run the Flutter app
+
+```bash
+flutter pub get
+```
+
+**Backend URL by platform** (`lib/services/api_service.dart` resolves this
+automatically, override with `--dart-define` if needed):
+
+| Target | Default URL used |
+|---|---|
+| iOS Simulator / macOS / Web dev server | `http://localhost:8000/api` |
+| Android Emulator | `http://10.0.2.2:8000/api` (auto-detected) |
+| Physical device | **must override** — your machine's LAN IP |
+
+```bash
+# Physical device example:
+flutter run --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.20:8000/api
+```
+
+```bash
+flutter run          # emulator/simulator/desktop
+flutter run -d chrome
+```
+
+## Notes on the scanning feature
+
+- Camera and photo-library permissions are declared for both Android
+  (`CAMERA`, runtime-requested via `image_picker`) and iOS
+  (`NSCameraUsageDescription`, `NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription`).
+- The backend never trusts the LLM alone for allergy safety: it also runs a
+  deterministic substring/cross-reactivity check (e.g. Penicillin ↔
+  Amoxicillin) against the user's recorded allergies before flagging a
+  conflict — defense in depth for a safety-relevant feature.
+- Scanned photos are stored under `backend/uploads/` and served at
+  `/uploads/<file>`; the Flutter app resolves this into a full URL via
+  `ApiService.resolveImageUrl`.
+
+## Deployment
+
+- **Backend**: containerized via `backend/Dockerfile`; swap SQLite for
+  Postgres by changing `DATABASE_URL` in `.env` (SQLAlchemy already
+  abstracts the engine — no code changes needed beyond the URL and driver).
+  Put it behind a reverse proxy (nginx/Caddy) with TLS in production, and
+  set `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` to your real app origin(s) instead of `*`.
+- **Flutter**: `flutter build apk` / `flutter build ios` / `flutter build web`,
+  always passing the production `--dart-define=API_BASE_URL=...`.
+
+## Known limitations (be upfront about these)
+
+- Single hardcoded demo user (`alex.rivera@medilens.com`) — no auth/session
+  system yet. The login/onboarding screens are UI-only.
+- SQLite is fine for local dev/demo; move to Postgres before any real
+  multi-user deployment.
+- AI scan results are not a substitute for professional medical or
+  pharmacist verification — this is enforced in the chat system prompt but
+  worth remembering as a product constraint, not just a code detail.
